    {
      "title": "Some more algebraic properties",
      "conceptBody": "<h3>Some more algebraic properties</h3><p>For the proof of this property we will approach from R.H.S.</p><p>Put $z=\\left( b-a \\right)x+a$ in R.H.S.</p><p>$\\Rightarrow \\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ dz}=\\left( \\text{b}-\\text{a} \\right)\\text{dx}$</p><p>&amp; when $\\text{x}=0$, $\\text{z}=\\text{a}$</p><p>$\\text{x}=1$, $\\text{z}=\\text{b}$</p><p>$\\therefore $ new integral becomes</p><p>$\\mathop{\\int }_{a}^{b}\\left( b-a \\right)f\\left( z \\right)\\frac{dz}{\\left( b-a \\right)}=\\mathop{\\int }_{a}^{b}f\\left( x \\right)dx=\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ L}\\text{.H}\\text{.S}\\text{. }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }$</p><p>some other properties.</p><ol><li>$\\int _{a}^{b}f\\left( x \\right)dx=\\int _{a+c}^{b+c}f\\left( x \\right)dx$</li><li>$\\int _{a}^{b}f\\left( x \\right)dx=\\int _{a-c}^{b-c}f\\left( x+c \\right)dx$</li></ol><p>or $\\int _{a}^{b}f\\left( x \\right)dx=\\int _{a+c}^{b+c}f\\left( x-c \\right)dx$</p><ol><li>$\\int _{a}^{b}f\\left( x \\right)dx=\\frac{1}{c}\\int _{a}^{b}f\\left( \\frac{x}{c} \\right)dx$</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Q) Evaluate $\\int _{-4}^{-5}{{e}^{{{(x+5)}^{2}}}}dx+3\\int _{1/3}^{2/3}{{e}^{9{{\\left( x-\\frac{2}{3} \\right)}^{2}}}}dx$&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Solution :&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>Note: Here we know $\\int {{e}^{{{x}^{2}}}}dx$ cannot be evaluated by indefinite integral&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Thus, $\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }{{I}_{1}}=\\int _{-4}^{-5}{{e}^{{{(x+5)}^{2}}}}dx$</p><p>$\\begin{array}{*{35}{r}} {} &amp; ~ =\\left( -5+4 \\right)\\mathop{\\int }_{0}^{1}{{\\text{e}}^{{{(\\left( -5+4 \\right)\\text{x}-4+5)}^{2}}}}\\text{ } \\\\ \\therefore \\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ } &amp; ~{{\\text{I}}_{1}}=-\\mathop{\\int }_{0}^{1}{{\\text{e}}^{{{(\\text{x}-1)}^{2}}}}\\text{dx} ...(i) \\\\ \\end{array}$</p><p>again, let</p><p>$\\begin{array}{*{35}{r}} {} &amp; ~{{I}_{2}}=\\mathop{\\int }_{1/3}^{2/3}{{\\text{e}}^{9{{(x-2/3)}^{2}}}}\\cdot dx \\\\ {} &amp; ~=\\left( \\frac{2}{3}-\\frac{1}{3} \\right)\\mathop{\\int }_{0}^{1}{{\\text{e}}^{9{{\\left[ \\left( \\frac{2}{3}-\\frac{1}{2} \\right)x+\\frac{1}{3}-\\frac{2}{3} \\right]}^{2}}}}\\cdot d\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ d}x \\\\ {} &amp; ~=\\frac{1}{3}\\mathop{\\int }_{0}^{1}{{\\text{e}}^{{{(\\text{x}-1)}^{2}}}}\\cdot \\text{dx} \\\\ {} &amp; ~=\\frac{1}{3}\\left( -{{\\text{I}}_{1}} \\right) ...(ii) \\\\ \\end{array}$</p><p>where, $\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }I={{I}_{1}}+3{{I}_{2}}$</p><p>$\\begin{matrix} ={{I}_{1}}+3\\left( -\\frac{{{I}_{1}}}{3} \\right) \\\\ ={{I}_{1}}-{{I}_{1}} \\\\ I=0 \\\\ \\therefore \\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }\\mathop{ \\int }_{-4}^{-5}{{e}^{{{(x+5)}^{2}}}}dx+3\\mathop{\\int }_{1/3}^{2/3}{{e}^{9{{(x-2/3)}^{2}}}}dx=0 \\\\ \\end{matrix}$</p>",
      "position": 0,
      "qcConcept": "66a0dd3ec03b9dcaf1afe9f9"
